The President of the United States congratulates Coptic Orthodox Christians and Egyptians on the selection of Bishop Tawadros as the 118th Pope of Alexandria and Patriarch of all Africa. The US shares Bishop Tawadros' commitment to unity, tolerance, and interfaith dialogue. They wish him success in leading the Middle East's largest Christian community during a time of change in the region. The US also reaffirms its support for religious freedom and mutual respect among people of all faiths. They will continue to stand with Egyptians of every faith as they work towards the goals of their revolution, including freedom, dignity, and economic opportunity.